metadata.name: Different Intersections - Iteration 4 #149
metadata.description:
This is the culmination of a series of iterations

____ - Iteration 1
____ - Iteration 2
____ - Iteration 3

The iterations were released under the pseudonym Extracurricular Activities.

The algorithmic theme of the iterations was extensive usage of boolean operations (intersection and difference) on polygons to derive interesting composite shapes.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Allégories booléennes #562
metadata.description:
"Allégories booléennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

This work is a continuation of research around the intersections of shapes that I have been exploring for a while. I wonder about the way in which they make it possible to bring out new compositions from superpositions of shapes that could initially represent a real disorder.

Controls:
• "a": Play the animation
• "s": Export the image (default 2160 × 3840px PNG)
• "h": Change export settings to high resolution (then press "s" to export a 6480 ×11520px PNG)
• "m": Change export settings to medium resolution (then press "s" to export a 4320 × 7680px PNG)
• "n": Back to 2160 × 3840px

Artwork by Julien Espagnon, 2022.

metadata.name: Landscapes out of my mind #227
metadata.description:
In this work, the third in the series of landscapes, I tried to achieve greater realism without abandoning those elements, also characteristic of the other works, which lead out of reality such as the shapes of the ground and trees and the choice of palettes.

Lands and Clouds are rendered using a mix of simplex noise and FBM (Fractional Brownian Motion), trees are generated with space colonization algorithm an placed using Poisson Disk Sampling distribution. The distribution density is driven by the land heightmap.


Developed with three.js using WebGLRenderer.
Rendering is faster with chrome browser.


[s] to save a png at 2048x1536, 1536x2048, 2048x2048 (4/3, 3/4, 4/4 aspect ratio)
[d] to save a png at 4096x3072, 3072x4096, 4096x4096 (4/3, 3/4, 4/4 aspect ratio)


Features:
"Palette": 14 colormaps
"Aspect Ratio": 4/3, 3/4, 4/4
"View Point":  Far, Medium, Near, Above
"Sky Type": FBM, Gradient1, Gradient2
"Sky Color": LightSkyBlue, Gray, Blue [10% probability]
"Bark Color":  Brown, GrayBrown, Gray
"Bare Trees": True, False


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Aliens #14
metadata.description:
"Aliens" is a collection derivated from "The Odd One Out" collection where you can see up close one of these some of its aliens:
- Longlorb: A slug-alien, not the most intelligent
- Skidle: A big mouth alien
- Trunglute: A mutated tree-alien
- Penclope: A cyclope alien with five tentacles
- NFT-Rex: An alien that may come from the dinoverse
- Blurp: An alien that will eat everything
- Booz: The main protagonist of the crowd, the one that needs to be find out

---------- CONTROLS -----------
- Double-click on the token to zoom into the picture (on Smartphone you can zoom normally)
- Right-click on the token to trigger download options (4 download options are available, low-res, normal-res, high-res and SVG), if you want to download a very high-fidelity of your token, I recommend the SVG option (Which you can then convert into PNG on various websites).

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 1 #412
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ 0.1, ____ 0.2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

metadata.name: Currency 5.0 #4
metadata.description:
Currency 5.0 is generative token commenting on the concept of value creation. The essential aspect of this process being that instead of the token being subjected to an arbitrary value determination and fluctuation, this token promises the minter that this "Coin" can always be reimbursed for the original mint value "till the artist is physically/mentally capable of performing this duty", hence this is also a long-form meta performative piece.

For this purpose a new dedicated wallet has been created (tz1N24vNXwcbmCRak3v83Qah5HaQn1xd768a), which promises to hold all the actual tezos generated for this purpose, in such a way that this exchange can be fulfilled.

Currency 5.0
@beardcoded Nov, 2022

metadata.name: Take Wing #11
metadata.description:
“Take Wing” is a generative art collection depicting the hope, optimism, and thrilling excitement of a person taking off, gaining traction, and soaring to new heights and off into the great unknown.  

The algorithm behind the piece stems from an attempt to go back to art fundamentals and codify composition rules and painterly techniques into a generative form - taking into account focal points, contrast, eye movement, and color theory while still giving the algorithm freedom to explore random color palettes, random flow field movement, random brush strokes, and many other degrees of freedom.

The collection is made in pure code with p5.js and a few GLSL fragment shaders.

The piece has been created to be exhibited at "In Touch" with VerticalCryptoArt in Berlin in September 2022, curated by Anika Meier.

------------------------------------------------

To get a (somewhat) high-resolution output, open the live view of your token, and then edit the URL adding &h=5400 at the end of it.  5400 is the tallest you can go, but you can also put a smaller number if you desire.  Be aware that this will only work on a machine with a very beefy GPU, and even then may take a bit, so please be patient!

metadata.name: Reflector #100
metadata.description:
REFLECTOR is an exploration of reflecting rays of light in two-dimensions by Juhani Halkomäki.

The pieces consist of 100 to 1200 rays of light that bounce two times when colliding with an object or the edge of the canvas. Some may seem more beautiful than others but they all have the same internals.

---
Features info
---

Dark mode - Paint the background black
Monochrome - No colors just grays
Emitter mode - One of the following: EDGE, SHAPE, POINT, GRID

Number Of Shapes - How many shapes are on the scene (1-4)
Number of Rays - How many rays are emitted (100-1000)
Number of Bounces - How many times the rays bounce (2-3)
Ray spreading - How much the ray angles are spread (10-100)

Color mode - Either SMOOTH or STEPS
Color spectrum size - How wide hue spectrum is used
Color spectrum offset - How much the hue is offset
Color step interval - How many consecutive rays should have the same color
Color step count - How many steps is the color spectrum divided into
